 observations to predict storms, temperature patterns, and climate trends.", "Thermodynamics is the branch of physics that deals with heat, work, temperature, and energy transfer in physical systems. Its four laws govern everything from heat engines to chemical reactions and the arrow of time."], "scores": [0.7815159551538203, 0.7179293274938278, 0.4303648067079524, 0.3927504131329779, 0.35987779178732343], "model_name": "mpnet", "document_ids": ["Astrophysics", "Astronomy", "Botany", "Meteorology", "Thermodynamics"]}}